  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nThe configuration for status-go node is built in multiple places, some of it comes from status-react, some of it from the react-native Status module, and finally some of it comes from status-go. This makes it difficult to update and to understand where each part is coming from.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nThe whole configuration should come from status-react, with the exception of platform specific values such as the log file path which will come from Status react-native module.\r\nStatic and default configuration such as the fleets configuration file available at https://fleets.status.im/ should be in the status-react repository and read from there by status-react.\r\n\r\nrelated issue on status-go side https://github.com/status-im/status-go/issues/1180\r\n\r\n# Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nstatus-react passes a nearly complete configuration file to .startNode method and Status react-native module doesn't make any changes beyond adding platform specific values to it.\r\n\r\n# Future Steps\r\n\r\nThe config building code can eventually be moved into a library that can be use to generate config files stored in a repo that can be passed to statusd standalone cli.\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote></blockquote>",
